    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Appointment
    Represents an appointment in a clinic system, storing information such as the date, timeslot, patient profile, and provider information.
    CircularLinkedList
    Represents a circular linked list that stores Technician objects.
    ClinicManager
    The ClinicManager class manages clinic operations, including scheduling, canceling, and rescheduling appointments.
    Date
    Represents a date with year, month, and day, and includes methods for validating the date, checking for leap years, and comparing dates.
    DateTest
     
    Doctor
    Represents a Doctor, which is a type of Provider with an associated specialty and a National Provider Identification (NPI) number.
    Imaging
    Represents an imaging appointment that extends the Appointment class.
    List<E>
    A generic dynamic array implementation of a list that allows for adding, removing, and accessing elements, along with iterator functionality.
    ListTest
     
    Location
    Represents various locations along with their corresponding county and zip code.
    Node
    A class representing a node in a linked list that holds a Technician object.
    Patient
    Represents a Patient, which is a type of Person with an associated visit history.
    Person
    Represents a person in the clinic system.
    Profile
    Represents a profile for a patient, including personal details such as name and date of birth.
    ProfileTest
     
    Provider
    Represents a Provider, which is an abstract class that extends Person.
    Radiology
    Enum representing the types of radiology services offered in the clinic.
    RunProject2
    The entry point for the Clinic Management application.
    Sort
    A utility class for sorting appointments and providers.
    Specialty
    Enum representing various medical specialties and their associated charges.
    Technician
    Represents a Technician, a type of Provider who performs medical procedures.
    Timeslot
    Represents a time slot for scheduling appointments with hour and minute fields.
    Visit
    Represents a visit in the clinic, which contains an appointment and a reference to the next visit.
